content.text: Decimal sub-multiples and multiples of units are indicated using a prefix to the unit. For example, the prefix milli (m) represents \(10^{- 3}\)
Which row gives the sub-multiples or multiples represented by pico (p) and giga (G)?
Density is mass per cubic metre
Potential difference is energy per unit current
Pressure is force per unit area
Speed is distance travelled per second
Which definition is correct and uses only quantities rather than units?
A force of 5.0 N pushes a ball due north and another force of 3.0 N pushes it due east
What is the magnitude of the net force acting on the ball?

The diagram shows an experiment to measure the speed of a small ball falling at constant speed through a clear liquid in a glass tube

There are two marks on the tube. The top mark is positioned at \(115 \pm 1 \text{mm}\) on the adjacent rule and the lower mark at \(385 \pm 1 \text{mm}\). The ball passes the top mark at \(1.50 \pm 0.02 \text{s}\) and passes the lower mark at \(3.50 \pm 0.02 \text{s}\)
The constant speed of the ball is calculated by \(\frac{385 - 115}{3.50 - 1.50} = \frac{270}{2.00} = 135 \text{mm} \text{s}^{-1}\)
Which expression calculates the fractional uncertainty in the value of this speed?

What is the total displacement of the ball from its original position after 1.5 s?

What are the weight and the mass of the body when it is on the Moon?

At which mark on the rule must a \(50 \text{g}\) mass be suspended so that the rule balances?
A steel sphere is dropped vertically onto a horizontal metal plate. The sphere hits the plate with a speed \(u\), leaves it at a speed \(v\), and rebounds vertically to half of its original height
Which expression gives the value of \(\frac{\nu}{u}\) ?

A block of mass \(2.0 \text{kg}\) is released from rest on a slope. It travels \(7.0 \text{m}\) down the slope and falls a vertical distance of \(3.0 \text{m}\). The block experiences a frictional force parallel to the slope of \(5.0 \text{N}\)
What is the speed of the block after falling this distance?

What is the average useful power at which he is working?

How many images of the slit does he see?
